          <p><%= link_to 'Windows XP/Vista/7/8 x32/x64', welcome_download_client_path(:type => 'Windows'), :class=>'btn btn-primary'%></p>
          <h4>Requirements</h4>
          <p>.Net Framework version 4 or better. Installer will load it automatically if not available</p>
          <p>If that doesn't work, you might have to download it manually</p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-mini" href="http://www.microsoft.com/net/download/version-4">Download .NET 4</a></p>
          <h4>Instructions</h4>
          <p>
            Download the file. Unzip it. Click 'Setup.exe'. Follow on-screen instructions
          </p>
          <p>
            <b>Note:</b>Windows XP may not recognize setup.exe. Click IdleTray.exe instead
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="span4">
      <div class="thumbnail">
        <img src="http://placehold.it/400x300" alt="" \>
        <div class="caption">
